	(text_box "The I2C address is hard-coded as 0x36h."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 349.25 187.96 0)
		(size 25.4 6.35)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type color)
			(color 251 255 120 1)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "18302cfa-2c92-4b20-bfed-508f5e487a44")
	)
	(text_box "Over-current protection: 1.5 A\n\nReverse polarity protection\n\nOvercharge detection: 4.28 V\nOver-discharge detection: 2.8 V\nDischarge overcurrent detection: 0.15 V\nCharge overcurrent detection: -0.1 V\nShort-circuit detection: 0.5 V"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 64.77 138.43 0)
		(size 62.23 26.6699)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2dabc522-e0f0-4614-80b9-f4fdfa15ae69")
	)
	(text_box "If V_BAT > V_5V0, V_SYS = V_BAT\nIf V_5V0 > V_BAT, V_SYS = V_BUS\n\nIf the board is powered from V_BAT, then ST is pulled high.\n\nIf the board is powered from V_BUS, then ST is pulled low."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 205.74 88.9 0)
		(size 35.56 20.3199)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2e3e7120-c106-4a24-807b-b9c222685270")
	)
	(text_box "The regulator is capable of sourcing 2 A @ V_{IN} = 3 V and 4 A @ V_{IN} = 5V.\n\nThe MCU draws approximately 100 mA in the worst-case scenario.\nThe modem draws approximately 500 mA in the worst-case scenario.\n\nThe values for the inductor and the feedback resistors are generated by the Texas Instruments' WEBENCH Power Designer tool with the following parameters: V_{IN}_MIN = 3.0 V, V_{IN}_MAX = 5.0 V, V_{OUT} = 3.7 V, I_{OUT}_MAX = 2 A."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 13.97 261.62 0)
		(size 149.86 21.59)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2e473f7e-2011-4c62-bc73-fe077c4a6d65")
	)
	(text_box "V_{DD} = 5V\nV_{BAT} = 3 V worst case\nI_{CHG} = 0.45 A\n\nMCP73833 datasheet:\nThermal resistance θ_{JA} is 41 °C/W.\nThermal shutdown T_{SD} is 150 °C.\nP = (5 V - 3 V) * I_{CHG} ~= 1 W\nMax temperature T_{CHG_MAX} = θ_{JA} * P = 41 °C\nT_{CHG_MAX} < T_{SD}"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 191.77 138.43 0)
		(size 62.23 26.67)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "3f0f7ae9-4ad2-4863-aa73-d79b28610c2e")
	)
	(text_box "A 1S 3.7V nominal LiPo battery can be used to power the device.\n\nWhen powered by the battery, the device typically consumes between 10 mA (in sleep mode) and 700 mA (during data transmission).\n\nThe charging current is 450 mA, so connect a battery with a capacity of at least 450 mAh.\n\nWhen powered via USB-C, the battery can be charged."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 13.97 138.43 0)
		(size 48.26 27.94)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "acd2e417-9ade-4227-b86e-d8b5815e4f28")
	)
	(text_box "To ensure that a depleted battery won't cause a sudden Brown-Out Reset (BOR), monitor the battery voltage and the State-of-Charge (SOC).\n\nFor ease of use, integrate a battery monitor that communicates with the host microcontroller using I2C."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 318.77 138.43 0)
		(size 63.5 20.32)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "e5917c36-3607-4d35-ab4e-9a9e70b0c7fa")
	)
	(text_box "Maximum desired discharge current is 1.5 A.\nTotal resistance across FETs should be\n0.15 V / 1.5 A = 100 mΩ.\n\nMaximum desired charge current is 1 A.\n100 mΩ * 1 A = 100 mV trigger level.\n\nR_{DS(ON)} @ 2.5 V_{GS} = ~9 mΩ\n9 mΩ * 2 = 18 mΩ\n\nR_{VSS} = 100 mΩ - 18 mΩ = 82 mΩ"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 127 139.7 0)
		(size 62.23 25.3999)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width -0.0001)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "e85ee324-3662-4120-9517-c79a8eae2a3e")
	)
	(text_box "The USB-C interface can be used to power the board, charge the battery and communicate with the microcontroller.\n\nWith 5.1 k pull-downs on the CC lines, the device is advertised as a downstream device.\n\nNOTE: The device can momentarily draw more than 500 mA so a USB-C to USB-A cable might not suffice."
